    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Columbia SC</placeName>
                <date>Jan 1867</date>
            </p>
            <p>Editor Occident</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Please find annexed a circular<lb/> which will explain its own
                mission. please insert the same in<lb/> your valuable Occident with such liberal
                remarks and recommendation<lb/> as the Laudable enterprise deserves. For if ever a
                community<lb/> stood in need of encouragement and support from Influential<lb/>
                quarters, The Israelites of this City come in for a full share__<lb/> For like the
                Dry Bones in the valley of <placeName>Hinom</placeName> we need the spirit<lb/> of
                God to <sic>ressurect</sic> and revive us for <add>אם ד' לא ישמור עיר שוא שקד
                    שומר</add></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">vain is the sentinels of vigilance if the Lord Guard not<lb/> the
                City„ Our work was commenced under the most unfavorable<lb/> auspices for we had not
                only to contend with and overcome the<lb/> different proclivities and
                predispositions of the various members of<lb/> which our <sic>divoted</sic> little
                Congregation is composed each <sic>claming</sic> to<lb/> enraft their own peculiar
                views. Imported from beyond the big seas<lb/> upon the Ancient land marks of our
                Sublime faith. But void as this<lb/> place has been for years past of Religion
                Religious Worship and instructions<lb/> Judaism stripped of her Holy and Ancient
                vestiges the last trace of our<lb/> Sublime inheritance allowed to fade from the
                Tablets of Memory of old<lb/> and young as does the last Golden Rays of the
                declining Sun when<lb/> Sinking to Rest. Our utmost endeavors had to be exerted to
                shake off<lb/> the heavy torpor and to dispose the deep gloom which like a
                dismal<lb/> mist did obscure that bright and shining light received upon
                    <persName>Sinaäs</persName><lb/> lofty brow. When first we met to Meditate upon
                a mode of action<lb/> How to rescue from oblivion the tottering and
                    <sic>smouldering</sic> pillow of</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>our ancient edifice we felt like <persName>Columbus</persName> when venturing out
                with<lb/> his devoted little <add>?</add> (Crew) in <date>1492</date> upon the
                turbulent and<lb/> unchartered mighty <placeName>Atlantic</placeName>. Many have
                pronounced it a Bold plan. And<lb/> though not as successful as him in making the
                voyage in two months<lb/> yet thank God the cry is Land-A-Hoy and our devoted little bark<lb/>
                <sic>strugling</sic> through the foaming billows Has heard the Haven of our
                long<lb/> anticipated desires and cast her anchor in gentle and placid waters<lb/>
                where the light of Heaven reflects a benign blessing around those<lb/> gathered
                under the Shadow of her wide expanded sails unfurled to the<lb/> breeze. Though our
                means and circumstances in life have been reduced<lb/> by the casualties and ravages
                of war yet with the help of Kind Heaven<lb/> and the assistance of a few of our
                coreligionists we have been<lb/> enabled to procure the services of a Chasan and
                Shackel and Rented<lb/> a place of worship where old and young can assemble to Praise<lb/>
                <placeName>Israels</placeName> God. We have also a Sunday School annexed to our
                Congregation<lb/> for the instruction of the Children of our Holy faith
                    <del>and</del> an Institution. That<lb/> has been <add>so much</add> needed and
                so long neglected. The Talented and Zealous <persName>Mrs<lb/> Charlotte. A.
                    Sevin</persName> has been <sic>electid</sic> President <persName>Mrs Jacob
                    Sevin</persName> Directress and<lb/>
                <persName>Mrs Branna Levy</persName> Vice President of the same and we are sanguine
                that with<lb/> the knowledge and ability these three talented Ladies are endowed
                with and the<lb/> success of their former Sunday School management that like the
                Pillar<lb/> of fire that led our ancestors through an uncultivated desert to
                lead<lb/> our offspring to a bright land of promise knowledge and bliss.</p>
            <p>
                <add>עורי עורי דבורה עורי עורי דברי שיר</add>
            </p>
            <p>Awake awake <persName>Deborah</persName> awake awake the inspired song. While talking
                of Ladies<lb/> We take the privilege of acknowledging the very liberal and
                munificent donation<lb/> of two Hundred and twenty five dollars from our Brethren of
                    <placeName>Charlotte</placeName><lb/>
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> and <placeName>Baltimore</placeName> through the
                kindness and untiring energy</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>of a highly esteemed Lady of our persuasion <persName>Mrs Elenor D Elias</persName> of<lb/>
                <placeName>Charlotte N. C.</placeName> long may she live to enjoy the blessings she
                so richly<lb/> deserves. Other remittances are acknowledged in the proper place. We
                have<lb/> formed a Constitution and By Laws upon strict orthodox principles<lb/> The
                following officers are elected for the ensuing year</p>
            <list type="simple">
                <head/>
                <item><persName>M. Winslock Esq</persName> President</item>
                <item><persName>S. Carr</persName>' Vice “</item>
                <item>
                    <persName>D. Epstin</persName>
                    <add>Trustee</add>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <persName>H. Sevin</persName>
                    <add>Trustee</add>
                </item>
                <item><persName>I. Davis</persName> Trustees</item>
                <item>
                    <persName>I. Dresden</persName>
                    <sic>Secetary</sic>
                </item>
            </list>
            <p>We had the pleasure of a visit from the Nestor of American Ministers<lb/>
                <persName>Rev <sic>Isaak</sic> Leeser</persName> on the <date>10th</date> inst and
                the gratification to listen<lb/> to words of wisdom and instruction from his gifted
                and fluent lips<lb/> and the vivid lightning flashes of his Brilliant and Prolific
                mind.<lb/> The meeting was well attended and the decorum and order observed<lb/> at
                the same showed that his instruction made a deep impression upon<lb/> the minds of
                his hearers and were relished</p>
            <p>
                <add>כשעירים עלי דשא וכרביבים עלי עשב דברים לב</add>
            </p>
            <p>Like a spray upon Herbs, as a shower upon grass.</p>
            <p>May kind Heaven prolong his life in his <sic>usefull</sic> career</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">With High regards I Have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">Sir yours very Respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">L. C</persName>
            </p>
            <p>
                <persName role="author">L Carr</persName>
            </p>
            <p>
                <placeName>Columbia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>S.C.</placeName>
            </p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
            <p>For Publication</p>
